{"questionId":"3397879","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the amount of money Angel would have at the end of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>5</mn></math> years with the bank. Give your answer correct to two decimal places.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1 (use of financial app in GDC)</strong></p>\n<table style=\"height:108px;width:272px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr style=\"height:110px;\">\n<td style=\"width:101.733px;height:110px;\">\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>%</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mn>520</mn></math><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"width:46.35px;text-align:center;height:110px;\"><strong>OR</strong></td>\n<td style=\"width:101.917px;height:110px;\">\n<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>N</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn></math><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>I</mi><mo>%</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mi>V</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>±</mo><mn>520</mn></math><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mo>/</mo><mi>Y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><em><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (M1)(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>M1</strong></em> for evidence of using the financial app on the calculator, <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for all correct entries.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>$</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>552</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>11</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award at most <em><strong>(M1)(A1)A0</strong></em> if correct answer is not given to two decimal places.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2 (use of formula)</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to substitute into compound interest formula&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>520</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mrow><mn>100</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mrow><mn>5</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mo>$</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>552</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>11</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award at most <em><strong>(M1)(A1)A0</strong></em> if correct answer is not given to two decimal places.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3397879","referenceCode":"23M.1.AHL.TZ2.4a","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the amount of money Angel would have at the end of 5 years with the bank. Give your answer correct to two decimal places.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.4—Financial apps – compound interest, annual depreciation","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.7—Loan repayments and amortization"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}